{
  "manifest": {
    "schemaVersion": 1,
    "name": "pomodoro",
    "title": "Pomodoro",
    "entrypoint": "index.html",
    "bindings": [],
    "capabilities": [
      "state:persist"
    ],
    "preferredSize": {
      "w": 3,
      "h": 5
    }
  },
  "files": {
    "README.md": "# Pomodoro\n\nA focus timer with work/break cycles, a depleting countdown ring, configurable\ndurations, and a completed-session counter — the second starter that persists\nits state across reloads via the `state:persist` capability.\n\n## What it demonstrates\n\n- **`state:persist`** — the `dashboard:getState` / `dashboard:setState` bridge\n  messages (identical envelope to `twenty48`). On boot it restores the phase,\n  the remaining seconds, the completed-session count, and the configured\n  work/break minutes; every meaningful change writes a tiny (<1 KB) blob back.\n- **Honest persistence** — a restored timer comes back **paused**. There is no\n  trustworthy elapsed-time source across an iframe remount, so it shows the\n  saved remaining time and lets you resume rather than silently drifting.\n- **Theme tokens** — reads `--bg` / `--card` / `--text` / `--accent` / `--border`\n  from the host's `dashboard:theme` reply and follows the background luminance\n  for its color scheme, so it looks right in both light and dark.\n- **No bindings, no network** — everything is self-contained in one sandboxed\n  HTML file.\n\n## Controls\n\n- **Start / Pause** — run or hold the current phase.\n- **Reset** — restore the current phase to its full length.\n- **Skip** — jump to the other phase without counting the current one.\n- **⚙ Settings** — configurable focus / break minutes, persisted with the rest\n  of the state.\n\nThe timer auto-advances at zero: a finished **Focus** phase increments the\nsession count and rolls into a **Break**, and vice versa.\n\n## Capability\n\n`state:persist` is declared in `widget.json`. Without the grant the parent\nreplies `capability_denied` and the timer runs in-memory (sessions reset on\nremount) — it never breaks, it just forgets.\n",
    "index.html": "<!doctype html>\n<!--\n  pomodoro — a work/break focus timer, and the SECOND starter that exercises the\n  `state:persist` capability end-to-end (twenty48 is the first). On boot it asks\n  the parent for its saved blob (dashboard:getState) and restores the phase, the\n  remaining seconds, the completed-session count, and the configured work/break\n  durations; whenever any of those change it writes a tiny blob back\n  (dashboard:setState). Both messages are gated by the \"state:persist\" capability\n  in widget.json — without it the parent replies capability_denied and the timer\n  just runs in-memory (sessions reset on remount). A restored timer comes back\n  PAUSED: there is no trustworthy wall clock across a remount, so we show the\n  saved remaining time and let you resume rather than silently drifting. No\n  bindings, no network of any kind: everything below is self-contained.\n-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n    <title>Pomodoro</title>\n    <style>\n      :root {\n        color-scheme: light dark;\n        /* Theme tokens: default to system Canvas/CanvasText, overridden by the\n           parent's dashboard:theme reply (--bg/--card/--text/--accent/--border).\n           Derived tokens read from --text so the pushed theme drives them. */\n        --bg: Canvas;\n        --card: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 8%, Canvas);\n        --text: CanvasText;\n        --accent: #e2504a;\n        --border: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 22%, transparent);\n        --muted: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 60%, transparent);\n        --track: color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 14%, transparent);\n        /* Phase colors: work leans on the theme accent; break is a calm green\n           that keeps contrast on both light and dark. */\n        --work: var(--accent);\n        --break: #2fa37a;\n      }\n      * {\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n      }\n      html,\n      body {\n        height: 100%;\n        margin: 0;\n      }\n      body {\n        padding: 10px;\n        font-family: var(--font-sans, system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif);\n        background: var(--bg);\n        color: var(--text);\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        gap: 8px;\n        user-select: none;\n        -webkit-user-select: none;\n      }\n      header {\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        gap: 6px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n      }\n      h1 {\n        margin: 0;\n        font-size: 1.05rem;\n        letter-spacing: 0.4px;\n        flex: 1;\n      }\n      .phase {\n        font-size: 0.6rem;\n        text-transform: uppercase;\n        letter-spacing: 0.8px;\n        font-weight: 700;\n        padding: 3px 8px;\n        border-radius: 999px;\n        color: #fff8f0;\n        background: var(--phase, var(--work));\n      }\n      .icon-btn {\n        font: inherit;\n        font-size: 0.95rem;\n        line-height: 1;\n        padding: 5px 8px;\n        border-radius: 6px;\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n        background: var(--card);\n        color: inherit;\n        cursor: pointer;\n      }\n      .icon-btn:hover {\n        border-color: var(--accent);\n      }\n      /* The ring scales to the smaller of the remaining width / height so it\n         always fits the widget cell regardless of aspect ratio. */\n      #stage {\n        flex: 1 1 auto;\n        min-height: 0;\n        display: flex;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        container-type: size;\n      }\n      #dial {\n        position: relative;\n        width: min(100%, 100cqh);\n        aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;\n        max-width: 100%;\n        max-height: 100%;\n      }\n      svg {\n        width: 100%;\n        height: 100%;\n        transform: rotate(-90deg);\n      }\n      .track {\n        fill: none;\n        stroke: var(--track);\n        stroke-width: 7;\n      }\n      .progress {\n        fill: none;\n        stroke: var(--phase, var(--work));\n        stroke-width: 7;\n        stroke-linecap: round;\n        transition:\n          stroke-dashoffset 0.3s linear,\n          stroke 0.2s ease;\n      }\n      .readout {\n        position: absolute;\n        inset: 0;\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        align-items: center;\n        justify-content: center;\n        gap: 2px;\n      }\n      .time {\n        font-size: 20cqmin;\n        font-weight: 700;\n        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n        line-height: 1;\n      }\n      .sessions {\n        font-size: 5.5cqmin;\n        opacity: 0.7;\n        letter-spacing: 0.4px;\n      }\n      .controls {\n        display: flex;\n        gap: 6px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n      }\n      .controls button {\n        font: inherit;\n        font-size: 0.8rem;\n        font-weight: 600;\n        padding: 7px 10px;\n        border-radius: 7px;\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n        background: var(--card);\n        color: inherit;\n        cursor: pointer;\n        flex: 1;\n      }\n      .controls button:hover {\n        border-color: var(--accent);\n      }\n      .controls .primary {\n        background: var(--phase, var(--work));\n        border-color: transparent;\n        color: #fff8f0;\n      }\n      /* Settings drawer — configurable, persisted work/break minutes. */\n      #settings {\n        display: none;\n        gap: 8px;\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        padding: 8px;\n        border-radius: 7px;\n        background: var(--card);\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n      }\n      #settings.show {\n        display: flex;\n      }\n      #settings label {\n        flex: 1;\n        display: flex;\n        flex-direction: column;\n        gap: 3px;\n        font-size: 0.6rem;\n        text-transform: uppercase;\n        letter-spacing: 0.5px;\n        opacity: 0.75;\n        font-weight: 600;\n      }\n      #settings input {\n        font: inherit;\n        font-size: 0.9rem;\n        width: 100%;\n        padding: 4px 6px;\n        border-radius: 5px;\n        border: 1px solid var(--border);\n        background: var(--bg);\n        color: inherit;\n      }\n      footer {\n        flex: 0 0 auto;\n        font-size: 0.62rem;\n        opacity: 0.6;\n        text-align: center;\n      }\n    </style>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <header>\n      <h1>Pomodoro</h1>\n      <span class=\"phase\" id=\"phase-label\">Focus</span>\n      <button class=\"icon-btn\" id=\"gear\" type=\"button\" title=\"Settings\" aria-label=\"Settings\">\n        ⚙\n      </button>\n    </header>\n\n    <div id=\"settings\">\n      <label\n        >Focus min\n        <input id=\"work-min\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" max=\"90\" step=\"1\" inputmode=\"numeric\" />\n      </label>\n      <label\n        >Break min\n        <input id=\"break-min\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" max=\"60\" step=\"1\" inputmode=\"numeric\" />\n      </label>\n    </div>\n\n    <div id=\"stage\">\n      <div id=\"dial\">\n        <svg viewBox=\"0 0 100 100\" aria-hidden=\"true\">\n          <circle class=\"track\" cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"45\" />\n          <circle class=\"progress\" id=\"ring\" cx=\"50\" cy=\"50\" r=\"45\" />\n        </svg>\n        <div class=\"readout\">\n          <div class=\"time\" id=\"time\">25:00</div>\n          <div class=\"sessions\" id=\"sessions\">0 sessions</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"controls\">\n      <button class=\"primary\" id=\"toggle\" type=\"button\">Start</button>\n      <button id=\"reset\" type=\"button\">Reset</button>\n      <button id=\"skip\" type=\"button\">Skip</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <footer>sandboxed · no network · state:persist</footer>\n\n    <script>\n      \"use strict\";\n\n      // ---- postMessage bridge helpers (v1 envelope, see packages/host/src/bridge.ts) ----\n      var reqSeq = 0;\n      function nextReqId() {\n        return \"pom-\" + Date.now().toString(36) + \"-\" + reqSeq++;\n      }\n      function post(type, extra) {\n        window.parent.postMessage(Object.assign({ v: 1, type: type }, extra || {}), \"*\");\n      }\n\n      // ---- timer state ----\n      var DEFAULTS = { workMin: 25, breakMin: 5 };\n      var workMin = DEFAULTS.workMin;\n      var breakMin = DEFAULTS.breakMin;\n      var phase = \"work\"; // \"work\" | \"break\"\n      var remaining = workMin * 60; // seconds left in the current phase\n      var running = false;\n      var sessions = 0; // completed focus sessions (persisted)\n      var ticker = null;\n\n      var CIRC = 2 * Math.PI * 45; // circumference of the r=45 ring\n\n      function phaseSeconds() {\n        return (phase === \"work\" ? workMin : breakMin) * 60;\n      }\n\n      // ---- rendering ----\n      var ringEl = document.getElementById(\"ring\");\n      var timeEl = document.getElementById(\"time\");\n      var sessionsEl = document.getElementById(\"sessions\");\n      var phaseEl = document.getElementById(\"phase-label\");\n      var toggleEl = document.getElementById(\"toggle\");\n      var dialEl = document.getElementById(\"dial\");\n\n      ringEl.style.strokeDasharray = CIRC;\n\n      function two(n) {\n        return (n < 10 ? \"0\" : \"\") + n;\n      }\n      function render() {\n        var total = phaseSeconds();\n        var mins = Math.floor(remaining / 60);\n        var secs = remaining % 60;\n        timeEl.textContent = two(mins) + \":\" + two(secs);\n        // Ring depletes as time runs down (full = time left, empty = done).\n        var frac = total > 0 ? remaining / total : 0;\n        ringEl.style.strokeDashoffset = CIRC * (1 - frac);\n\n        var color = phase === \"work\" ? \"var(--work)\" : \"var(--break)\";\n        dialEl.parentElement.style.setProperty(\"--phase\", color);\n        document.documentElement.style.setProperty(\"--phase\", color);\n        phaseEl.textContent = phase === \"work\" ? \"Focus\" : \"Break\";\n        sessionsEl.textContent = sessions + (sessions === 1 ? \" session\" : \" sessions\");\n        toggleEl.textContent = running ? \"Pause\" : \"Start\";\n      }\n\n      // ---- timer engine ----\n      function tick() {\n        if (remaining > 0) {\n          remaining -= 1;\n          render();\n          if (remaining <= 0) advancePhase();\n          else if (remaining % 15 === 0) saveState(false); // periodic durable checkpoint\n        }\n      }\n\n      // A phase reached zero: count a completed focus session, flip work<->break,\n      // and roll straight into the next phase (classic pomodoro auto-advance).\n      function advancePhase() {\n        if (phase === \"work\") sessions += 1;\n        phase = phase === \"work\" ? \"break\" : \"work\";\n        remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n\n      function start() {\n        if (running) return;\n        if (remaining <= 0) remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        running = true;\n        ticker = setInterval(tick, 1000);\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n      function pause() {\n        if (!running) return;\n        running = false;\n        if (ticker) {\n          clearInterval(ticker);\n          ticker = null;\n        }\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n      function toggle() {\n        if (running) pause();\n        else start();\n      }\n      function reset() {\n        pause();\n        remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n      function skip() {\n        // Jump to the other phase without counting the current one as complete.\n        phase = phase === \"work\" ? \"break\" : \"work\";\n        remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        render();\n        saveState(true);\n      }\n\n      // ---- settings (configurable, persisted durations) ----\n      var settingsEl = document.getElementById(\"settings\");\n      var workInput = document.getElementById(\"work-min\");\n      var breakInput = document.getElementById(\"break-min\");\n\n      function syncInputs() {\n        workInput.value = workMin;\n        breakInput.value = breakMin;\n      }\n      function clampMin(value, fallback, hi) {\n        var n = Math.round(Number(value));\n        if (!isFinite(n) || n < 1) return fallback;\n        return n > hi ? hi : n;\n      }\n      function applySettings() {\n        var nextWork = clampMin(workInput.value, workMin, 90);\n        var nextBreak = clampMin(breakInput.value, breakMin, 60);\n        var changed = nextWork !== workMin || nextBreak !== breakMin;\n        workMin = nextWork;\n        breakMin = nextBreak;\n        // A running phase keeps counting down; an idle/full phase adopts the new\n        // length immediately so the change is visible without a reset.\n        if (!running && remaining >= phaseSeconds()) remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        if (remaining > phaseSeconds()) remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        syncInputs();\n        render();\n        if (changed) saveState(true);\n      }\n\n      document.getElementById(\"gear\").onclick = function () {\n        settingsEl.classList.toggle(\"show\");\n      };\n      workInput.addEventListener(\"change\", applySettings);\n      breakInput.addEventListener(\"change\", applySettings);\n\n      // ---- state:persist (dashboard:getState / dashboard:setState) ----\n      var saveTimer = null;\n      var haveState = false; // did the parent ever answer? (else run in-memory)\n      function serialize() {\n        return {\n          phase: phase,\n          remaining: remaining,\n          sessions: sessions,\n          workMin: workMin,\n          breakMin: breakMin,\n        };\n      }\n      function saveState(immediate) {\n        if (saveTimer) {\n          clearTimeout(saveTimer);\n          saveTimer = null;\n        }\n        var doSave = function () {\n          saveTimer = null;\n          post(\"dashboard:setState\", { requestId: nextReqId(), state: serialize() });\n        };\n        if (immediate) doSave();\n        else saveTimer = setTimeout(doSave, 500);\n      }\n\n      function restore(state) {\n        haveState = true;\n        if (!state || typeof state !== \"object\") return false;\n        if (typeof state.workMin === \"number\")\n          workMin = clampMin(state.workMin, DEFAULTS.workMin, 90);\n        if (typeof state.breakMin === \"number\")\n          breakMin = clampMin(state.breakMin, DEFAULTS.breakMin, 60);\n        if (state.phase === \"break\" || state.phase === \"work\") phase = state.phase;\n        if (typeof state.sessions === \"number\" && state.sessions >= 0)\n          sessions = Math.floor(state.sessions);\n        if (typeof state.remaining === \"number\" && state.remaining >= 0) {\n          remaining = Math.min(Math.floor(state.remaining), phaseSeconds());\n        } else {\n          remaining = phaseSeconds();\n        }\n        // Always resume paused — there is no trustworthy elapsed-time source across\n        // a remount, so we never silently keep counting down.\n        running = false;\n        return true;\n      }\n\n      // ---- theme ----\n      // Relative luminance (0..1) of a #rgb / #rrggbb color; null for anything non-hex.\n      function hexLuminance(value) {\n        if (typeof value !== \"string\" || value.charAt(0) !== \"#\") return null;\n        var hex = value.slice(1);\n        if (hex.length === 3) hex = hex[0] + hex[0] + hex[1] + hex[1] + hex[2] + hex[2];\n        if (!/^[0-9a-fA-F]{6}$/.test(hex)) return null;\n        var r = parseInt(hex.slice(0, 2), 16);\n        var g = parseInt(hex.slice(2, 4), 16);\n        var b = parseInt(hex.slice(4, 6), 16);\n        return (0.2126 * r + 0.7152 * g + 0.0722 * b) / 255;\n      }\n      function applyTheme(tokens) {\n        if (!tokens) return;\n        var root = document.documentElement.style;\n        [\"--bg\", \"--card\", \"--text\", \"--accent\", \"--border\", \"--muted\"].forEach(function (k) {\n          if (tokens[k]) root.setProperty(k, tokens[k]);\n        });\n        var lum = hexLuminance(tokens[\"--bg\"]);\n        if (lum !== null) root.colorScheme = lum < 0.5 ? \"dark\" : \"light\";\n      }\n\n      // ---- inbound messages (ignore anything without the v:1 envelope) ----\n      var stateReqId = nextReqId();\n      window.addEventListener(\"message\", function (event) {\n        var msg = event.data;\n        if (!msg || msg.v !== 1) return;\n        if (msg.type === \"dashboard:theme\") {\n          applyTheme(msg.tokens);\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:state\") {\n          // reply to our boot getState (or the echo of a setState). Only the first,\n          // matching our boot getState, seeds the timer.\n          if (!haveState && msg.requestId === stateReqId) {\n            restore(msg.state);\n            syncInputs();\n            render();\n          }\n        } else if (msg.type === \"dashboard:error\") {\n          // capability_denied (state:persist off) or similar — fall back to an\n          // in-memory timer so the widget still works when opened standalone.\n          if (!haveState) haveState = true;\n        }\n      });\n\n      // ---- wire up + boot ----\n      document.getElementById(\"toggle\").onclick = toggle;\n      document.getElementById(\"reset\").onclick = reset;\n      document.getElementById(\"skip\").onclick = skip;\n\n      syncInputs();\n      render();\n\n      // Announce, request theme, and ask for our persisted blob. If no host is\n      // listening (standalone open) nothing replies — we simply run in-memory.\n      post(\"dashboard:ready\");\n      post(\"dashboard:getTheme\", { requestId: nextReqId() });\n      post(\"dashboard:getState\", { requestId: stateReqId });\n      setTimeout(function () {\n        if (!haveState) haveState = true; // standalone: no host, keep defaults\n      }, 400);\n    </script>\n  </body>\n</html>\n"
  }
}
